view: Box beats Dropbox \u2013 and all the rest \u2013 for business | publisher=InfoWorld | date=6 November 2013 | accessdate=12 July 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | last = Duffy | first= Jill  | url= https://www.pcmag.com/article2/0,2817,2410914,00.asp | title= Box (Personal) Review & Rating | publisher=PCMag | accessdate=12 July 2014}}</ref>\n| <!--Storage size--> {{some|}}free trial,<br>100 GB paid (Starter),<br>Unlimited Business,<br>Unlimited Enterprise<ref name=\":0\">{{Citation | url = https://www.box.com/pricing/ | publisher = Box | title = Plans & Pricing | accessdate = 20 July 2016}}.</ref>\n| <!--Max. file size--> {{rarely|}}250&nbsp;MB free Personal,<br>5&nbsp;GB paid Personal,<br>5 GB Business,<br>5 GB Enterprise<ref name=\":0\" />\n| <!--Traffic/bandwidth limit--> {{some|}}10&nbsp;GB/month free,<br>2 TB/month paid<ref>{{Citation | contribution-url = https://support.box.com/entries/21543487-What-is-the-bandwidth-limit- | contribution = What is the bandwidth limit? | title = Support | publisher = Box | accessdate = 7 August 2013}}.</ref>\n| <!--Remote uploading--> {{some|}} 30&nbsp;MB per file via IFTTT<ref>{{cite web| title=Upload file from URL - Box | url=https://ifttt.com/channels/box/actions/72-upload-file-from-url | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170317153513/https://ifttt.com/channels/box/actions/72-upload-file-from-url | url-status=dead | archive-date=17 March 2017 |website=IFTTT (archived)| publisher=IFTTT| accessdate=22 January 2019}}</ref>\n| <!--Developer API?--> {{yes}}<ref>{{cite web | url=https://developers.box.com/ | title= Platform Developer Documentation | publisher=Box | accessdate= 15 December 2013}}</ref>\n| <!--FTP upload possible--> {{some|}} Business and Enterprise customers only<ref>{{cite web | url = https://support.box.com/hc/en-us/articles/200520058-FTP-Details | title=I\u2019m having trouble using FTP with Box | publisher =Box | accessdate= 15 December 2013}}</ref>\n| <!--File versioning--> {{some}} (premium)<ref>{{ci