entaro Sakaguchi]] as Riku Hasegawa\n\n===Supporting===\n{{colbegin}}\n* [[Ryo Ryusei]] as Naoya Matsuda\n* [[Erina Mano]] as Rina Sagara\n* Yuki Izumisawa as Tetta Nakamura\n* [[Rina Ohta]] as Kaoru Obara, a graduate student of physics\n* Keiko Horiuchi as Keiko Hinata, Aoi's mother\n* Goro Oishsi as a professor\n* [[Seiichi Tanabe]] as Shuntaro Hasegawa, Riku's uncle and foster parent.\n{{colend}}\n\n==Original soundtrack==\nThe film's soundtrack was on [[Oricon Albums Chart]] for six weeks and peaked at #25.<ref>{{cite web |script-title=ja:\u6620\u753b\u300c\u541b\u3068100\u56de\u76ee\u306e\u604b\u300d\u30aa\u30ea\u30b8\u30ca\u30eb\u30fb\u30b5\u30a6\u30f3\u30c9\u30c8\u30e9\u30c3\u30af|url=http://contents.oricon.co.jp/prof/74438/products/1212245/1/|website=Oricon |language=ja}}</ref>\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = {{Nihongo|'''''The 100th Love with You'''''|\u541b\u3068100\u56de\u76ee\u306e\u604b|Kimi to 100 Kaime no Koi}} <br /> <small>Original Soundtrack</small>\n| type       = Soundtrack\n| artist     = Various Artists\n| cover      =\n| alt        =\n| released   = January 25, 2017\n| recorded   =\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Soundtrack]], [[Ballad]], [[Pop music|Pop]]\n| length     =\n| label      = [[Sony Music Entertainment Japan|Sony Music Japan]]\n| producer   = Naoki Yoshitake\n| prev_title =\n| prev_year  =\n| next_title =\n| next_year  =\n}}\n\n===Selected tracks===\n* {{nihongo|\"The 100th Love with You\"|\u541b\u3068100\u56de\u76ee\u306e\u604b|\"Kimi to Hyakkaime no Koi\"}} by [[Miwa (singer)|Miwa]]\n* {{nihongo|\"Aiokuri\"|\u30a2\u30a4\u30aa\u30af\u30ea}} by The STROBOSCORP\n* {{nihongo|\"Simple Feelings\"|\u5358\u7d14\u306a\u611f\u60c5|\"Tanjun na Kanjo\"}} by The STROBOSCORP\n* \"Birthday Morning\" by And\u014dzu\n* \"BGM\" by [[Androp]]\n* \"27\" by [[Super Beaver]]\n\n==Home media==\nThe film's Blu-ray (Limited Edition) BD+BD (SRXW-2/3), Blu-ray (SRXW-4), DVD (Limited Edition) DVD + DVD (SRBW-41/42), DVD (SRBW-43) was released on June 23, 2017 by [[Asmik Ace]]\n\n==Reception==\n===Box office===\nThe film premiered in 190 screens, and opened at #5 in the box office with 73,352 admissions.<ref>{{cite web |script-title=ja:\u30c6\u30a3\u30e0\u30fb\u30d0\u30fc\u30c8\u30f3\u300e\u30df\u30b9\u30fb\u30da\u30ec\u30b0\u30ea\u30f3\u300f\u5973\u6027\u30d5\u30a1\u30f3\u306e\u71b1\u72c2\u7684\u652f\u6301\u30671\u4f4d\uff01|url=https://www.cinematoday.jp/news/N0089482|website=[[Cinema Today]] |language=ja}}</ref>\n\n===Reception===\nIt ranked #1 in [[:ja:|PIA Corporation]]'s audience satisfaction survey.<ref>{{cite web |script-title=ja:miwa\uff06\u5742\u53e3\u5065\u592a\u90ce\u30c0\u30d6\u30eb\u4e3b\u6f14\u300e\u541b\u3068100\u56de\u76ee\u306e\u604b\u300f\u304c\u6e80\u8db3\u5ea6\u30e9\u30f3\u30ad\u30f3\u30b0\u7b2c1\u4f4d\uff01|url=http://cinema.pia.co.jp/news/170202/69598/|website=Pia |language=ja}}</ref>\n\n==Adaptation==\n===Manga===\nA three-volume manga adaptation ({{ISBN|978-4-08-890577-8}}, {{ISBN|978-4-08-890578-5}}, {{ISBN|978-4-08-890596-9}}) by Yoshiduki Kumichi \"Kimi was released on Young Jump Comics, [[Shueisha]]\n\n===Novel===\nTwo novelizations, by Orange Bunko ({{ISBN|978-4-08-680114-0}})<ref>{{cite web |script-title=ja:\u541b\u3068\uff11\uff10\uff10\u56de\u76ee\u306e\u604b\u3000\u6620\u753b\u30ce\u30d9\u30e9\u30a4\u30ba|url=https://www.e-hon.ne.jp/bec/SA/Detail?refShinCode=0100000000000033535813&Action_id=121&Sza_id=LL|website=e-hon |language=ja}}</ref> and Mirai Bunko ({{ISBN|978-4-08-680114-0}})<ref>{{cite web|script-title=ja:\u541b\u3068100\u56de\u76ee\u306e\u604b|url=http://miraibunko.jp/book/koi/book044/|website=Miraibunko |language=ja}}</ref> were released\n\n===Remake===\nIn July 2017, Linekong Pictures Corporation acquired the rights of the film for a Chinese-language adaptation.<ref>{{cite web|script-title=ja:miwa\uff06\u5742\u53e3\u5065\u592a\u90ce\u4e3b\u6f14\u306e\u604b\u611b\u6620\u753b\u3001\u4e2d\u56fd\u3067\u30ea\u30e1\u30a4\u30af\u3078|url=https://www.cinematoday.jp/news/N0092638|website=[[Cinema Today]] |language=ja}}</ref>\n\n==Spin-off==\nWritten by Satomi Oshima the one-volume {{nihongo|''Kimi to Ikkaime no Koi''|\u541b\u30681\u56de\u76ee\u306e\u604b|The 1st Love with You}}, {{ISBN|978-4-08-745564-9}}, was released as spin-off of the film\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://kimi100.com/ Official site]\n*{{IMDb title|tt5614984}}\n*[http://eiga.com/movie/84695/ The 100th Love with You] on [[Eiga]]\n*{{Facebook|kimi100movie}}\n*{{Twitter|kimi100movie}}\n*{{Instagram|kimi100movie}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:100th Love With You, The}}\n[[Category:Japanese films]]\n[[Category:2017 films]]\n[[Category:Japanese-language films]]\n[[Category:Japanese romantic drama films]]\n[[Category:Japanese fantasy films]]\n[[Category:Films about time travel]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Sh\u014d Tsukikawa]]\n[[Category:Shueisha manga]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox film\n| name           = The 100th Love with You\n| image          = The 100th Love with You poster.jpg\n| director       = [[:ja:\u6708\u5ddd\u7fd4|Sho Tsukikawa]]\n| writer         = [[:ja:\u5927\u5cf6\u91cc\u7f8e|Satomi Oshima]]\n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| film name      = {{Infobox name module\n|kanji          = \u541b\u3068100\u56de\u76ee\u306e\u604b\n|romaji         = Kimi to 100 Kaime no Koi\n|translation    = \n}}\n| starring       = [[Miwa (singer)|Miwa]]<br />[[Kentaro Sakaguchi]]\n| music          = Goro Ito\n| distributor    = [[Asmik Ace]]\n| released       = {{Film date|2017|02|04}}\n| runtime        = 116 minutes\n| language       = |\n}}\n{{Nihongo|'''''The 100th Love with You'''''|\u541b\u3068100\u56de\u76ee\u306e\u604b|'''''Kimi to 100 Kaime no Koi'''''|lead=yes}} is a [[Japanese language|Japanese]] [[Romantic fantasy|romantic-fantasy]] film starring [[Miwa (singer)|Miwa]] and [[Kentaro Sakaguchi]], with original screenplay by [[:ja:\u5927\u5cf6\u91cc\u7f8e|Satomi Oshima]] and direction by [[:ja:\u6708\u5ddd\u7fd4|Sho Tsukikawa]].<ref>{{cite web |script-title=ja:miwa\u3068\u5742\u53e3\u5065\u592a\u90ce\u304c\u300c\u541b\u3068100\u56de\u76ee\u306e\u604b\u300d\u3067W\u4e3b\u6f14\u3001\u6642\u3092\u304b\u3051\u308b\u30e9\u30d6\u30b9\u30c8\u30fc\u30ea\u30fc|url=https://natalie.mu/eiga/news/182592|website=Natalie |language=ja}}</ref> It premiered in Japan on February 4, 2017, and was also released in other territories including China and South Korea.\n\n{{ external media\n| video1 =[http://kimi100.com ''The 100th Love with You'' Trailer]\n}}\n\n==Synopsis==\nOn July 31, university student Aoi Hinata ([[Miwa (singer)|Miwa]]) had a traffic accident. When she wakes up, Aoi Hinata finds herself in a classroom a week before. Her childhood friend Riku Hasegawa ([[Kentaro Sakaguchi]]) then tells her that he can turn back time.\n\n==Cast==\n===Main===\n* [[miwa (singer)|Miwa]] as Aoi Hinata\n* [[Kentaro Sakaguchi]] as Riku Hasegawa\n\n===Supporting===\n{{colbegin}}\n* [[Ryo Ryusei]] as Naoya Matsuda\n* [[Erina Mano]] as Rina Sagara\n* Yuki Izumisawa as Tetta Nakamura\n* [[Rina Ohta]] as Kaoru Obara, a graduate student of physics\n* Keiko Horiuchi as Keiko Hinata, Aoi's mother\n* Goro Oishsi as a professor\n* [[Seiichi Tanabe]] as Shuntaro Hasegawa, Riku's uncle and foster parent.\n{{colend}}\n\n==Original soundtrack==\nThe film's soundtrack was on [[Oricon Albums Chart]] for six weeks and peaked at #25.<ref>{{cite web |script-title=ja:\u6620\u753b\u300c\u541b\u3068100\u56de\u76ee\u306e\u604b\u300d\u30aa\u30ea\u30b8\u30ca\u30eb\u30fb\u30b5\u30a6\u30f3\u30c9\u30c8\u30e9\u30c3\u30af|url=http://contents.oricon.co.jp/prof/74438/products/1212245/1/|website=Oricon |language=ja}}</ref>\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = {{Nihongo|'''''The 100th Love with You'''''|\u541b\u3068100\u56de\u76ee\u306e\u604b|Kimi to 100 Kaime no Koi}} <br /> <small>Original Soundtrack</small>\n| type       = Soundtrack\n| artist     = Various Artists\n| cover      =\n| alt        =\n| released   = January 25, 2017\n| recorded   =\n| v